<li id="fn75"><p>I would instinctively read this as ‚ÄúI return again (despite what I intended)‚Äù. Maybe ‚ÄúI have returned again.‚Äù Or ‚Äúthe film has returned‚Ä¶‚Äù Or ‚ÄúEva returns‚Ä¶‚Äù. Any thoughts on this? ^^ Might need the original context.<a href="#fnref75">‚Ü©</a></p></li>
<li id="fn76"><p>„ÄåÂÖ®Ë®òÈå≤ÂÖ®ÈõÜ Â∫è„Äç„ÅÆÂ∫µÈáéÁßÄÊòéÁ∑èÁõ£Áù£„Å∏„ÅÆÂèñÊùêÊôÇ„ÅÆÂç∞Ë±°„Å®ÈÅï„ÅÜ„Åü„ÇÅ„ÄÅ„Åì„ÅÜ„ÅÑ„ÅÜËÅû„ÅçÊñπ„ÅßÊéò„Çä‰∏ã„Åí„Å¶„ÅÑ„Çã„ÄÇ<a href="#fnref76">‚Ü©</a></p></li>
<li id="fn77"><p>[Mr.] Hikawa, who assisted with the advertising for ‚ÄúPrelude‚Äù, had seen a few of the drafts of the designs for the ‚ÄúStairs Poster‚Äù that became a key visual [for the ‚ÄúRebuild‚Äù films]; however, none of them honestly struck him. One day, when he was shown the version of the poster with various ‚Äúkey words‚Äù written horizontally across it, he received the impression ‚ÄúSuddenly, it‚Äôs become ‚ÄòEva‚Äô!‚Äù and forthrightly communicated his shock to the people in charge at that time. That version was not contributed by the designer. Hideaki Anno had personally directed his assistant, Ikki Todoroki, to create it. When this came out, Hikawa experienced a second shock and made the remark in question. (See page 305 of Ikki Todoroki‚Äôs interview.)<a href="#fnref77">‚Ü©</a></p></li>
<li id="fn78"><p>„ÅÑ„Å§„ÇÇ„Éü„Çπ„Çø„Éº„Éª„Ç®„É¥„Ç°„ÅåÂ∏∏„Å´„Çπ„Ç§„ÉÉ„ÉÅ„ÇíÂ•Ω„Åç„Å™Êñπ„Å∏ÂÄí„Åó„Å¶„Åç„Åü„Å£„Å¶„Åì„Å®„Åß„Åô„Å≠„ÄÇ<a href="#fnref78">‚Ü©</a></p></li>
<li id="fn79"><p>According to 2 Anno interviews in 2011 &amp; 2012, this is literal: Anno personally funded the development of Khara &amp; <em>Rebuild</em>. ‚ÄìEditor<a href="#fnref79">‚Ü©</a></p></li>
